@startuml curve_pipeline
' Revised 2026-05-13: applied audit_23/Wave-1-fix amendments
!include dark-theme.puml
title Environmental-curve pipeline - sun/time inputs to per-monitor target to apply\nOwned by EnvironmentalCurveService; SliderState is the per-row gate

participant "EnvironmentalCurveService\n._curveTimer (DispatcherTimer Background,\n interval = AppSettings.EnvironmentalCurveTickIntervalMs\n clamped to 250ms..60s)"  as TIM
participant "EnvironmentalCurveService\n._curveEventThrottleTimer\n(trailing-edge, BrightnessUpdateRateMs)"  as THR
participant "EnvironmentalCurveService\n.Evaluate / .ApplyAt(t)"                       as EC
participant "ProfileManager\n(SelectedIndex,\n SelectedProfileChanged)"                 as PM
participant "EnvironmentalCurve\n(stored on profile)"                                   as STORED
participant "AppSettings\n(Latitude / Longitude /\n EnvironmentalOffsetMode /\n EnvironmentalCurveSmoothness)" as APP
participant "SunShifter\n(src/Utils)"                                                   as SS
participant "SPACalculator\n(src/SunriseSunset)"                                        as SPA
participant "EnvironmentalCurveSampler\n(src/Utils)"                                    as ECS
participant "SliderStateMachine\n(pure transition fns,\n in src/Models/MonitorInfo.cs)" as SSM
participant "MonitorInfo\n(.SliderState,\n .CurveTargetBrightness,\n .Brightness, .Offset)" as MI
participant "MonitorService\n.EnqueueDirectBrightness"                                  as MSE
participant "NightLightProvider\n.SetStrength(persistAsLastUserValue: false)"           as NLP
participant "BrightnessFlyout\n(toggle owner,\n preview-sweep driver)"                  as BFL
participant "App / User"                                                                  as USER

== Engagement flag write path (canonical 9-step sequence) ==
note over BFL, APP
  Sole writer: BrightnessFlyout setter for IsBrightnessCurveEnabled / IsNightLightCurveEnabled.
  All steps run synchronously on the UI dispatcher.
  Flyout constructor seeds backing fields DIRECTLY (line 321) - setters bypassed at startup.
end note
USER -> BFL : click curve toggle\n(per-row icon, footer, or absolute-mode slider mousedown un-toggle)
BFL  -> BFL : step 1: equality check (skip if unchanged)
BFL  -> BFL : step 2: capture wasOn
BFL  -> BFL : step 3: _isBrightnessCurveEnabled = value (flyout mirror)
BFL  -> EC  : step 4: _curveService.IsBrightnessCurveEnabled = value (auto-prop, no event)
BFL  -> APP : step 5: AppSettings.EnvironmentalBrightnessCurveEnabled = value
BFL  -> APP : step 6: AppSettings.Save (best-effort - swallows IO exceptions)
BFL  -> BFL : step 7: OnPropertyChanged (XAML chrome refresh)
BFL  -> EC  : step 8: OnCurveToggleStateChanged ->\n  Engage/Disengage + CaptureOffsetsFromMaster (engage-on only) + Start() + Evaluate()
BFL  -> MSE : step 9 (if wasOn && !value): ResyncBrightnessHardwareToSliders

== Inputs ==
note over TIM, APP
  Two driver paths into Evaluate():
  - Periodic: _curveTimer.Tick fires Evaluate while a curve resolves.
  - Event-driven: settings-window edits call BFL.RequestCurveReevaluation,
    which calls service.RequestEvaluation; first call schedules
    _curveEventThrottleTimer to fire Evaluate at +BrightnessUpdateRateMs;
    further calls in-window fold into the pending fire.
  Suspend()/Resume() pause both timers for the 24h preview sweep, which
  drives ApplyAt(t) directly with a simulated day-fraction.
end note

TIM -> EC : Tick
THR -> EC : trailing-edge fire (settings edit)
BFL -> EC : ApplyAt(t)\n(preview sweep, 50ms cadence)

== Resolve current curve ==
EC -> PM     : SelectedIndex
EC -> STORED : profile.EnvironmentalCurve\n(ResolveStoredCurve)
EC -> EC     : ResolveLiveCurve\n(check FollowTheSun &&\n cached source/date/lat/lon/DST\n against AppSettings)

alt FollowTheSun off OR (lat == 0 AND lon == 0) OR\n stored.BrightnessAnchor.Date == default
  EC -> EC : return stored as live\n(no shift)
else cache miss (key axis differs)
  EC -> SS  : BuildPreview(stored, fromAnchor, toAnchor)
  SS -> SPA : GetSunTimes(lat, lon, refDateTimeOffset)\nx2 (from-date, to-date)
  SPA --> SS : SunTimes\n(twilights, sunrise, solar noon, sunset)
  SS -> SS  : BuildAnchorArray (11 entries)\n[0, astroDawn, nautDawn, civilDawn,\n sunrise, solarNoon, sunset,\n civilDusk, nautDusk, astroDusk, 1]\nMissing twilights synthesized at +/-1s
  SS -> SS  : ShiftPoints (per-list, segment-relative remap)\nfor Brightness, NightLight,\nBrightnessOffset, NightLightOffset
  SS --> EC : sun-shifted EnvironmentalCurve\nstored in _cachedShiftedCurve\n+ (Date, Lat, Lon, DST, sourceRef) cache key
else cache hit
  EC -> EC : reuse _cachedShiftedCurve
end

note right of EC
  Cache key: (sourceCurveRef, **Version**, Date, Lat, Lon, DST).
  EnvironmentalCurve.Version int bumps on every mutation (H-28 fix);
  a future mutation path that bypasses NotifyRuntimeCurveChanged
  would no longer silently keep the pre-edit shape until midnight.
  Invalidation triggers today:
   - ProfileManager.SelectedProfileChanged -> InvalidateCurveCache
     (now fires immediate Evaluate - M-03 fix).
   - RequestEvaluation nukes _cachedShifted* unconditionally.
   - SystemEvents.TimeChanged subscription invalidates the cache
     on clock / DST jumps (M-01 fix).
end note

== Time + disabled-period read ==
EC -> ECS : t = CurrentDayFraction()\n(local TimeOfDay / 24, [0,1))
EC -> ECS : inDisabled = IsInDisabledPeriod(stored, t)
note right of ECS
  Disabled-period uses STORED curve, not live.
  SunShifter.ClonePoints does not carry
  DisabledPeriod* fields, and the period
  has its own (independent) SunAnchor.
  Wrap-midnight handled inside the sampler.
end note
EC -> BFL : onDisabledPeriodChanged(inDisabled)\n(updates IsInCurveDisabledPeriod)

== Per-tick state harmonization (HarmonizeRow) ==
loop foreach m in _monitors
  alt brightness curve engaged
    EC -> SSM : HarmonizeRow(m, inDisabledPeriod, curveEngaged=true)
    note right
      switch m.SliderState:
        Enabled        -> CurveActive (curveEngaged) or CurveSleeping (inDisabled)
        CurveActive    -> CurveSleeping if inDisabled
        CurveSleeping  -> CurveActive if !inDisabled
        CurveReleased  -> CurveReleased (PRESERVED at default arm)
        Disabled       -> unchanged
        Failed         -> unchanged (HarmonizeRow gates on IsHardwareFunctional /\n                     IsHardwareFailed - H-27)
    end note
  end
end
alt night-light curve engaged
  EC -> SSM : HarmonizeRow on _nightLightMonitor
end
SSM -> MI : SliderState writes\n(CurveReleased / Disabled / Failed untouched)
MI --> BFL : PropertyChanged (one event for SliderState\nplus IsCurveDriven, IsCurveSleeping,\n IsHardwareFunctional, etc.)

== Sleep-enter one-shot resync ==
alt sleepEntering (false -> true since last tick)
  loop foreach MonitorInfo m in _monitors
    alt m.SliderState == CurveSleeping
      EC -> MSE : EnqueueDirectBrightness(m, m.RoundedBrightness)
    end
  end
  alt night-light row sleeping AND NightLightProvider.IsSupported
    EC -> NLP : SetStrength(\n  flipIfNightLightInverted(roundedBrightness),\n  persistAsLastUserValue: false)
  end
  note right of EC
    Curve relinquishes hardware to the user's
    slider. Without this push, the bus stays
    frozen at the last curve write through
    the sleep window.
  end note
end

== Brightness curve apply (if IsBrightnessCurveEnabled) ==
note over EC: smoothness = AppSettings.EnvironmentalCurveSmoothness/100\nabsolute = !AppSettings.EnvironmentalOffsetMode

alt absolute mode
  EC -> ECS : Sample(curve.Brightness, t, smoothness)\n(monotonic-cubic Hermite blended with linear)
  EC -> MI  : master.CurveTargetBrightness = sample\n(clamped 0..100; gated on master.IsCurveDriven - H-29)
  loop foreach m in _monitors
    alt m.IsCurveDriven (Active or Sleeping)
      EC -> MI  : m.CurveTargetBrightness = sample + m.Offset
    end
    alt m.SliderState == CurveActive AND !m.IsDragging
      EC -> MSE : EnqueueDirectBrightness(m, round(sample + m.Offset))
    end
  end
else offset mode
  EC -> ECS : Sample(curve.BrightnessOffset, t, smoothness)
  EC -> EC  : offsetPercent = (sample - 50) * 2  (-> [-100,+100])
  EC -> MI  : master.CurveTargetBrightness = master.LastUserBrightness + offsetPercent
  loop foreach m in _monitors
    alt m.IsCurveDriven
      EC -> MI  : m.CurveTargetBrightness = m.LastUserBrightness + offsetPercent
    end
    alt m.SliderState == CurveActive AND !m.IsDragging
      EC -> MSE : EnqueueDirectBrightness(m, round(m.LastUserBrightness + offsetPercent))
    end
  end
end

alt brightness curve disengaged
  EC -> SSM : DisengageBrightnessCurveStates\n(Curve* -> Enabled; Disabled / Failed stick)
end

== Night-light curve apply (if IsNightLightCurveEnabled and supported) ==
alt NightLightProvider.IsSupported()
  alt absolute mode
    EC -> ECS : Sample(curve.NightLight, t, smoothness)
    EC -> EC  : strength = clamp(round(sample), 0..100)\nsliderPos = flipIfNightLightInverted(strength)
    alt nightLight row IsCurveDriven
      EC -> MI : nightLight.CurveTargetBrightness = sliderPos
    end
    alt nightLight.SliderState == CurveActive
      EC -> NLP : SetStrength(strength, persistAsLastUserValue: false)
    end
  else offset mode
    EC -> ECS : Sample(curve.NightLightOffset, t, smoothness)
    EC -> EC  : strengthOffsetPercent = (sample - 50) * 2  (-> [-100,+100])\ncurStrength = flipIfNightLightInverted(rounded)\ntargetStrength = clamp(curStrength + offsetPct)
    alt nightLight row IsCurveDriven
      EC -> MI : nightLight.CurveTargetBrightness =\n  flipIfNightLightInverted(targetStrength)
    end
    alt nightLight.SliderState == CurveActive
      EC -> NLP : SetStrength(targetStrength,\n  persistAsLastUserValue: false)
    end
  end
else backend unavailable
  EC -> SSM : DisengageNightLightCurveStates
end

== Out-of-band SliderState transitions (not in Evaluate) ==
BFL -> SSM : OnUserToggleOff / OnUserToggleOn\n(group-membership icon click)
BFL -> SSM : OnUserRelease (drag a curve-driven individual)\nOnUserReengage (double-click released individual)
BFL -> EC  : EngageBrightnessCurveStates /\nEngageNightLightCurveStates /\nDisengage* (OnCurveToggleStateChanged)
EC  -> SSM : OnCurveEngaged / OnCurveDisengaged per row
MSE -> SSM : OnHardwareFailed / OnHardwareRecovered\n(MonitorService write/verify path)
BFL -> EC  : Suspend / Resume / ApplyAt(t)\n(preview sweep)

note over TIM
  Service lives independent of the flyout window.
  Curves drive monitors and night-light even
  when the flyout is hidden. BrightnessFlyout
  observes MonitorInfo.PropertyChanged for
  Brightness / SliderState / CurveTargetBrightness.
end note

note over MI
  SliderState is the single source of truth
  for what each row is doing right now.
  Setter coalesces PropertyChanged so a single
  state change emits one event for SliderState
  plus one for each derived computed bool
  (IsHardwareFunctional, IsCurveDriven,
   IsCurveSleeping, etc.).
end note

note over NLP
  Slider-release SetStrength still calls in
  parallel with curve-driven SetStrength.
  Curve writes pass persistAsLastUserValue: false
  so curve samples never overwrite the user's
  remembered "last warmth" for restore-on-toggle.
end note

== Disabled-period master propagation (FIXED - H-04) ==
USER -> BFL : drag MasterMonitor slider during _isInCurveDisabledPeriod == true
BFL  -> MSE : SuspendHardwareWrites() {
BFL  -> MI  :   ApplyMasterToEnabledMonitors writes each individual's Brightness
MI   -> MSE :   OnMonitorPropertyChanged subscribers - _hardwareWritesSuspendCount > 0,\n  short-circuit before OnUserRelease
BFL  -> MSE :   EnqueueDirectBrightness(m, target) DIRECTLY per individual
BFL  -> MSE : } ResumeHardwareWrites()
note right of MSE
  Wave-1 fix: disabled-period master propagation is wrapped in
  SuspendHardwareWrites; OnMonitorPropertyChanged sees suspendCount > 0
  and skips the OnUserRelease(CS) -> CR transition. Direct
  EnqueueDirectBrightness pushes the user's master value to the bus
  while individuals STAY in CurveSleeping. When the disabled period
  ends, HarmonizeRow promotes them back to CurveActive cleanly.
end note

note right of TIM
  Start() arming sites:
   - BrightnessFlyout ctor end (UNCONDITIONAL - M-02 fix:\n     timer arms even with both curve flags persisted OFF)
   - OnCurveToggleStateChanged (per toggle)
   - OnAppSettingsChanged (per settings save)
  With M-02 closed, _isInDisabledPeriod is computed live on every
  tick regardless of curve-flag state. Disabled-period flags do not
  go stale through the lifetime of a session.
end note

@enduml
